  "prompt": "How long does it take to open a savings bank account in ICICI bank?",
  "response": "The time it takes to open a savings bank account with ICICI Bank can vary based on several factors, such as the type of account, the completeness of your documentation, and whether you are opening the account online or in person. Generally, here are the typical scenarios:\n\n1. **In-Person at a Branch:** \n   - This can often be done on the same day if you visit a branch with all the required documents (such as proof of identity, proof of address, and recent photographs). The bank staff will verify your documents, assist with filling out the application, and may open the account immediately.\n\n2. **Online:**\n   - Opening an account online can be quick, often just taking a few minutes to complete the application. However, final approval and activation might take a few days, as there might be additional verification processes, such as a video KYC (Know Your Customer) or submission of documents.\n\n3. **Document Verification:**\n   - Whether opened online or in person, the account might be activated quicker if all your documents are in order. Any discrepancies or incomplete documentation might delay the process.\n\nAlways check with ICICI Bank for the latest requirements and estimated processing times, as procedures and timelines can change. It might also be helpful to use their customer service or online resources for precise guidance tailored to your situation.",
